verbose_text: Basic fibroblast growth factor (FGF-2) is reported to be a strong mitogen and acts on various cell types, including HOBs, MSCs and hPDLCs, in addition to being effective in accelerating the proliferation of fibroblasts and osteoblasts, and enhancing angiogenesis.
